			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2021</a> keynote:</span><br><i>Live Programming and Programming by Example: Better Together</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/SorinLerner.html">Sorin Lerner</a></h2>
<ul><li>URL: <a href="https://conf.researchr.org/details/gpce-2021/gpcegpce+2021+-+20th+international+conference+on+generative+programming%3A+concepts+%26+experiences2021/17/GPCE-Keynote-Live-Programming-and-Programming-by-Example-Better-Together">https://conf.researchr.org/details/gpce-2021/gpcegpce+2021+-+20th+international+conference+on+generative+programming%3A+concepts+%26+experiences2021/17/GPCE-Keynote-Live-Programming-and-Programming-by-Example-Better-Together</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagM">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> The keynote is about interactive environments that provide continual execution feedback and synthesize code from examples, i.e., advanced programming support tooling.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4g.html"><span class="tagL">T4G: AI-for-SLE</span></a><ul><li> Programming-by-example in this context is fundamentally synthesis/AI-style automation driven by examples, so AI techniques are central to the contribution.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t5h.html"><span class="tagL">T5H: Usability</span></a><ul><li> The core motivation is improving the programmer experience via continual feedback and higher-level interaction (examples instead of manual coding).
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4d.html"><span class="tagL">T4D: Interpretation</span></a><ul><li> Live programming hinges on runtime execution and continuous observation of values during program execution.
</li></ul></li></ul>
